https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Strava-Monthly-Stats-March10-e6179a9.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=816%2C543 2x\"><source media=\"(min-width: 590px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Strava-Monthly-Stats-March10-e6179a9.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C370\" type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Strava-Monthly-Stats-March10-e6179a9.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C370\"><source media=\"(min-width: 590px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Strava-Monthly-Stats-March10-e6179a9.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C370\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Strava-Monthly-Stats-March10-e6179a9.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C370\"><img data-src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Strava-Monthly-Stats-March10-e6179a9.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=620%2C413\" width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Strava monthly stats\" title=\"Strava Monthly Stats - March10\" src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Strava-Monthly-Stats-March10-e6179a9.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=620%2C413\"></picture></div><meta itemprop=\"url\" content=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Strava-Monthly-Stats-March10-e6179a9.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=768%2C574\"><meta itemprop=\"width\" content=\"768\"><meta itemprop=\"height\" content=\"574\"></div><div><p>Published: <time datetime=\"2021-03-10T18:00:29+00:00\">March 10, 2021 at 6:00 pm</time></p><meta itemprop=\"datePublished\" content=\"2021-03-10T18:00:29+00:00\"><meta itemprop=\"dateModified\" content=\"2021-03-10T18:01:06+00:00\"><p></p></div></header><section itemprop=\"articleBody\"><p><span>Stravaâ€™s My Year in Sport feature is always a highlight of the year end, telling you how much closer to the moon the distance you rode got you, how many Everests you climbed, how many days you actually got off your sofa and such like.</span></p><p><span>Itâ€™s a bit of a motivator to maybe jump on the bike and head off into the big wide world a bit more in the coming year.</span></p><ul><li><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/news/strava-year-in-sport/\">Strava Year in Sport review shows that women drove doubling of activities logged in 2020</a></li></ul><p><span>Now you can have that end of year experience more often because <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/brand/strava/\">Strava</a> now offers its premium subscribers an animated run-through of their activities every month.</span></p><p><span>Like My Year in Sport, the Monthly Stats animation will only be available in the Strava mobile app on Android and iOS via the Profile tab. It will provide a more visual output of the stats that Strava currently emails out monthly.</span></p><p><span>As with many of its enhanced features, including the changes to <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/news/strava-personal-heatmap/\">personal heatmaps</a> made in January, the Monthly Stats feature will only be fully available to Strava users paying a <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/news/strava-leaderboards-routes-subscription/\">monthly subscription</a>, although free users will get a limited preview of their stats.</span></p><p><span>The new Monthly Stats feature is one of a stream of updates that Strava is making to the app, as it looks to revamp the experience and make more features available to its paying subscribers.</span></p><p><span>Maybe seeing that you cycled 500km less last month than the previous one will motivate you to get out a bit more. Or maybe youâ€™ll just sink further into your sofa and trawl Netflix for yet another series youâ€™ve missed. Itâ€™s your choice.</span></p></section><section><h3>Authors</h3><section><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/author/paulmnorman/\"><img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/11/Head-shot-PMN-d98e93a.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=60,60\" srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/11/Head-shot-PMN-d98e93a.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=120,120 120w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/11/Head-shot-PMN-d98e93a.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=60,60 60w,\" sizes=\"(max-width: 60px) 100vw, 60px\" width=\"60\" height=\"60\" alt=\"Paul Norman\" title=\"Paul Norman\"></a><p>Paul has been riding since he was a teenager and has been writing about bike tech for almost five years. He was into gravel before it was even invented, riding a cyclocross bike across the South Downs and along muddy paths through the Chilterns. He dabbled in cross-country mountain biking too, before returning to drop bar bikes.</p></section></section><section><h3>Tags</h3><ul><li><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/brand/strava/\">Strava</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/cycling-discipline/gravel/\">Gravel</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/cycling-discipline/mtb/\">Mountain Biking</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/cycling-discipline/road/\">Road Cycling</a></li></ul></section></div><section><h3>You may also like</h3></section></article></div></div>","author":"Paul Norman","siteTitle":"BikeRadar","siteHash":"df99dd1320fcd97327a2def4c67247c08cd4090a7dab684a0eddb9b856f80ef1","entryHash":"af9e9f756e4db7f79bbbbf9d764c8fedc2bdd9b94adc1415ed81afa59bea2e13","category":"Cycling"}